# EtherChannel (LACP)

## Objective
Bundle the redundant links between coreSW1‚ÜîSwitch1 and coreSW1‚ÜîSwitch2 into single logical links using LACP to increase bandwidth and provide link redundancy.

## Design
Two EtherChannel bundles were created ‚Äî Po1 between coreSW1 and Switch1, and Po2 between coreSW1 and Switch2. Each bundle consists of two physical links configured as LACP active on both sides.

## What I Configured
- Configured both physical links on each side as trunk ports with all VLANs allowed
- Created EtherChannel bundle between coreSW1 and Switch1 using LACP
- Created EtherChannel bundle between coreSW1 and Switch2 using LACP
- Verified STP still recognizes coreSW1 as root and sees the bundles as single logical links

## Troubleshooting
- Ports were not showing in `show interfaces trunk` because they were administratively shut down ‚Äî had to enable them first
- EtherChannel Po2 was not coming up because trunk mode and VLAN allowance were not configured on the physical ports before creating the bundle ‚Äî always configure trunk settings first, then create the EtherChannel

